snippet.textDisplay: Zeb Bangash has become a symbol of cheerful, memorable performances in coke studio. I did not know Faakhir Mehmood before, he brought lots of energy in to the song, and kudos to him for the concept. This is expected from coke studio pakistan- brilliance in concept and execution withour much fuss. Finally, the backing vocalists are a treat to watch, it is visible that they had lots of fun in supporting the leads. It is hard not to feel festive.

This song has many shortcomings i.e. Poor Pashtu accent (since the singers are non-Pakhtoon); secondly, they are singing something involving tragedy and yet they express so much euphoria ! Its just like singing: Hell yeah my mum died ! yahoo ! 

Overall, poor performance. There should have been a native Pashtu speaker who could guide them.
